### pgauthzd NATIVE + AuthZEN read API examples against the demo model.
###
### Target: the pgauthzd front door. These requests use BOTH surfaces:
###   * native  POST /pgauthz/v1/*   (vendor read API: check, list-*, explain, watch)
###   * AuthZEN POST /access/v1/*    (spec-compliant evaluation/search + discovery)
###
### PORTS (published by compose-authzen.yml):
###   * :8090  pgauthzd-decision (decision-only, read-only DB role)
###            — serves BOTH the native /pgauthz/v1 reads AND the AuthZEN surface.
###            This is the right front door for this file → @baseUrl below.
###   * :8092  pgauthzd-full — also serves both (writer role); use for reads too.
###   * :8091  pgauthzd-opa (compat-opa) — serves the AuthZEN surface ONLY; the
###            native /pgauthz/v1 endpoints are NOT here (they live on OPA's
###            internal callback listener) and return 404 on :8091.
### So point @baseUrl at :8090 for the full read surface; switch to :8091 only
### for the /access/v1 requests if you want the OPA-fronted (policy) path.
###
### AUTH: every request needs a valid JWT (401 otherwise). The pre-minted demo
### tokens live in http-client.env.json (select the "dev" environment):
### {{access_token_alice}}, {{access_token_bob}}, {{access_token_carl}}. They are
### ES256-signed with opa/keys/demo.key.txt (iss https://auth.example.com, aud
### authz-api). Mint fresh ones with tests/test-authzen.sh's make_token helper,
### or from Keycloak via keycloak/get-token.sh.
### NOTE: the demo/test stack runs with ALLOW_SUBJECT_OVERRIDE=true (set in
### env.sh), so the request-BODY subject is authoritative and any valid demo
### token authenticates the call. In a secure token-only deployment the JWT
### subject wins and a mismatched body subject is rejected with 403.
###
### Requires: docker compose up (bootstrap.sh) with compose-authzen.yml.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8090
@token = {{access_token_alice}}

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — SINGLE ACCESS CHECK  (POST /pgauthz/v1/check)
### Policy-free raw graph decision. Response: { "allowed": <bool> }
### =====================================================================

### Alice can read the payroll document (via payroll_team membership)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "allowed": true }

###

### Alice cannot read the tax document (wrong team)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_tax_001" }
}
### Expected: { "allowed": false }

###

### Rich result — detail:true carries state/missing_context/model
### Response: { "allowed": <bool>, "detail": { "state": "allow|deny|conditional", ... } }
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" },
  "detail":   true
}
### Expected: { "allowed": true, "detail": { "state": "allow", ... } }

###

### Contextual tuples — ephemeral grant, evaluated but never persisted.
### Frank has no stored tuple; the contextual viewer tuple grants access
### for THIS request only. Elements use the write_tuples_jsonb shape.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "frank" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_client_001" },
  "contextual_tuples": [
    {
      "user_type":   "internal_user",
      "user_id":     "frank",
      "relation":    "viewer",
      "object_type": "document",
      "object_id":   "doc_client_001"
    }
  ]
}
### Expected: { "allowed": true } (contextual tuple is not stored)

###

### Store-scoped (tenant) variant — the /stores/{store} path selects the store.
### Same body, minus any need for the X-PGAuthz-Store header / DEFAULT_STORE.
POST {{baseUrl}}/stores/demo/pgauthz/v1/check
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "allowed": true }

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — BATCH CHECK  (POST /pgauthz/v1/check-batch)
### Shared subject/action/resource defaults merge into each check.
### Response: { "results": [ <bool>, ... ] } (in order)
### =====================================================================

### Multiple checks for Alice in a single round-trip
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check-batch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "checks": [
    { "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "action": { "name": "can_edit" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_tax_001" } }
  ]
}
### Expected: { "results": [true, true, false] }

###

### deny_on_first_deny — short-circuits at the first false (semantic on the batch)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/check-batch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },
  "semantic": "deny_on_first_deny",
  "checks": [
    { "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_acc_001" } }
  ]
}
### Expected: { "results": [false, ...] } (short-circuited after the first deny)

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — LIST OBJECTS  (POST /pgauthz/v1/list-objects)
### "Which resources of a type can the subject act on?"
### Only resource.type is used. Response: { "objects": [ ... ], "next_token"? }
### =====================================================================

### Which documents can Bob read?
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/list-objects
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_bob}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document" }
}
### Expected: { "objects": [ ...5 doc ids... ] }

###

### Keyset pagination — first page (limit=2). Follow next_token for the next page.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/list-objects
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_bob}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document" },
  "limit": 2
}
### Expected: { "objects": [id1, id2], "next_token": "..." }

###

### Next page — pass the previous response's next_token via "after".
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/list-objects
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_bob}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document" },
  "limit": 2,
  "after": "PASTE_next_token_HERE"
}
### Expected: the following page of object ids

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — LIST SUBJECTS  (POST /pgauthz/v1/list-subjects)
### "Which subjects of a type can act on the object?"
### Only subject.type is used. Response: { "subjects": [ ... ], "next_token"? }
### =====================================================================

### Which internal users can read the payroll document?
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/list-subjects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "subjects": [ "alice", "bob", ... ] }

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — LIST ACTIONS  (POST /pgauthz/v1/list-actions)
### "What can the subject do on the object?"  Response: { "actions": [ ... ] }
### =====================================================================

### What can Alice do on the payroll document?
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/list-actions
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "actions": ["can_edit", "can_read"] }

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — EXPLAIN  (POST /pgauthz/v1/explain)
### The structured "why": returns explain_access's JSON verbatim
### ({ "decision": { "allowed": <bool> }, "trace": [...], ... }).
### =====================================================================

### Full resolution trace — why Alice can read the payroll doc
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/explain
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "decision": { "allowed": true }, "trace": [ ... ] }

###

### Explain a denied access — why Eva cannot read the payroll doc
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/explain
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "decision": { "allowed": false }, "trace": [ ... ] }

###

### =====================================================================
### NATIVE — WATCH  (POST /pgauthz/v1/watch)
### Cursored page of the store's audit changefeed (HTTP transport over
### authz.watch_changes). The connection role needs auditor privileges.
### Response: { "events": [ ... ], "next_cursor": { "after_at", "after_seq" } }
### =====================================================================

### Most recent changes (first page)
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "limit": 5
}
### Expected: { "events": [...], "next_cursor": { "after_at": "...", "after_seq": N } }

###

### Filtered + cursored — only document/viewer changes after a cursor.
### Feed after_at/after_seq back from the previous response's next_cursor.
POST {{baseUrl}}/pgauthz/v1/watch
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "limit": 10,
  "object_types": ["document"],
  "relations": ["viewer"],
  "after_seq": 0
}
### Expected: { "events": [ ...matching changes... ], "next_cursor": { ... } }

###

### =====================================================================
### AuthZEN 1.0 — SINGLE EVALUATION  (POST /access/v1/evaluation)
### Spec surface. Response: { "decision": <bool> }
### =====================================================================

### Alice can read the payroll doc
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/evaluation
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "decision": true }

###

### Rich decision context — opt in with the X-PGAuthz-Detail header.
### Response gains a "context" object (state, missing_context, ...).
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/evaluation
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
X-PGAuthz-Detail: true
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "decision": true, "context": { "state": "allow", ... } }

###

### Store-scoped evaluation (tenant PDP): /stores/{store}/access/v1/evaluation
POST {{baseUrl}}/stores/demo/access/v1/evaluation
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "decision": true }

###

### =====================================================================
### AuthZEN 1.0 — BATCH EVALUATIONS  (POST /access/v1/evaluations)
### Shared subject/action/resource merge into each evaluation.
### Response: { "evaluations": [ { "decision": <bool> }, ... ] }
### =====================================================================

### Alice: can_read + can_edit but not can_delete on the payroll doc
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/evaluations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "evaluations": [
    { "action": { "name": "can_read" },   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "action": { "name": "can_edit" },   "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "action": { "name": "can_delete" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } }
  ]
}
### Expected: { "evaluations": [ {"decision":true}, {"decision":true}, {"decision":false} ] }

###

### Mixed subjects + deny_on_first_deny semantic
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/evaluations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "semantic": "deny_on_first_deny",
  "evaluations": [
    { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "eva" },   "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } },
    { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" }, "action": { "name": "can_read" }, "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" } }
  ]
}
### Expected: { "evaluations": [ {"decision":false}, ... ] } (short-circuited)

###

### =====================================================================
### AuthZEN 1.0 — SEARCH  (subject / resource / action)
### These may be gated by SEARCH_REQUIRED_ROLE (not set in the test stack).
### =====================================================================

### SUBJECT SEARCH — who can read the payroll doc? (subject.type fixed)
### Response: { "results": [ { "subject": { "type", "id" } }, ... ], "page"? }
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/search/subject
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "results": [ { "subject": { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" } }, ... ] }

###

### RESOURCE SEARCH — which documents can Bob read? (resource.type fixed)
### Response: { "results": [ { "resource": { "type", "id" } }, ... ], "page"? }
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/search/resource
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_bob}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document" }
}
### Expected: { "results": [ ...5 documents... ] }

###

### RESOURCE SEARCH with keyset pagination — page size 1, then follow page.next_token
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/search/resource
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_bob}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "bob" },
  "action":   { "name": "can_read" },
  "resource": { "type": "document" },
  "page":     { "size": 1 }
}
### Expected: { "results": [ one ], "page": { "next_token": "..." } }

###

### ACTION SEARCH — what can Alice do on the payroll doc?
### Response: { "results": [ { "action": { "name" } }, ... ] }
POST {{baseUrl}}/access/v1/search/action
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subject":  { "type": "internal_user", "id": "alice" },
  "resource": { "type": "document", "id": "doc_payroll_001" }
}
### Expected: { "results": [ { "action": { "name": "can_edit" } }, { "action": { "name": "can_read" } } ] }

###

### =====================================================================
### AuthZEN 1.0 — DISCOVERY  (GET, no auth required)
### =====================================================================

### PDP metadata document (AuthZEN §9.1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/.well-known/authzen-configuration
### Expected: { "policy_decision_point": "...", "access_evaluation_endpoint": ".../access/v1/evaluation", ... }

###

### Tenant (path-insertion) discovery — scopes the PDP to /stores/demo (§9.2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/.well-known/authzen-configuration/stores/demo
### Expected: identifiers + endpoints all carry the /stores/demo path
